    <id>http://joanperals.com/2014/big-bother</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>Big Bother</em> is watching you&hellip; and you too.</p>

<!--more-->


<p><em>Big Bother</em> (sic) is a generative sketch that features an eye on a large screen. This eye has the ability to mutate a little when it detects movement around: a new pupil appears to follow every &ldquo;target&rdquo;, with the aim to follow each watcher individually.</p>

<p>This piece was exhibited on a huge screen in the center of Madrid as part of <a href="http://programalaplaza.medialab-prado.es/">MediaLab Prado&rsquo;s #ProgramaLaPlaza</a>Â contest in 2014.</p>

<!--more-->




<iframe src="//player.vimeo.com/video/100365334#t=31m09s?autoplay=0" height="632" width="100%" allowfullscreen="" frameborder="0"></iframe>


<p>You can check and tweak the code <a href="http://programalaplaza.medialab-prado.es/sketch/view/975a0c44be49772e59f0d3872a8a618f">here</a>, and see other submitted projects <a href="http://programalaplaza.medialab-prado.es/static/2014.html">here</a>.</p>
